title: Four Section IV Class D teams ranked ahead of playoffs
text:
Four Section IV Class D teams ranked ahead of playoffs 
By wbng sports Four Section IV Class D teams ranked ahead of playoffs October 21, 2015 Updated Oct 21, 2015 at 6:33 PM EDT 
(WBNG Binghamton) Four of the eight Section IV Class D teams playing in this week's sectional quarterfinals are ranked in the latest New York Sportswriters Association football rankings this week. 
Two-seed Deposit/Hancock ranks the highest of all of them at fourth in the state, while Section IV No. 1 seed Tioga comes in at No. 6. 
The two other Section IV Class D teams ranked in the state rankings play each other in a quarterfinal this weekend. Ninth ranked Walton plays 13th ranked Harpursville/Afton for the right to move onto the semifinals on Saturday. 
Elsewhere, both Maine-Endwell and Chenango Forks remained No. 1 in the state in their respective classes.
